deck_excerpt: This could be the best rouge deck on the internet
deck_description:
the first cards you want to stat off with either your going second or first is either 1 of the 2 live twin monsters or cynet mining to add one to your hand. then summon one and activate its effect to special out of the deck the other live twin monster. Then at this point you will need to make a decision based on if you went first or second. if you went first link into kiskil then summon from the grave the other live twin to then link into lilla to then activate her effect summoning back kiskil (the link monster) to then draw a card. if you went second do what i just said but with the other twins. But the end effect will be to destroy a card on the field. then i would either link those two into unchained abomination and see if you have a unchained trap in hand to set it then end then activate abomination to pop it or to pop an opponents card. All the trap cards have primary effects that do different things but they all have similar secondary effects. these effects allows you to summon an unchained monster from the hand, deck or grave if the trap gets destroyed by card effect. This also counts for your own cards destroying them. This is the main strategies for the unchained monsters. Ive added to the deck some XYZ coverage with Numbers 97, 107 and 38 all rank 8. these can be summoned by the two level 8 monsters in the deck which are:

Abominable Unchained Soul

and

Unchained Soul of Disaster.

If you are going to XYZ summon then i would go into number 97 as he can summon (by its effect) one of the other rank 8 monsters by attaching the other to it as an XYZ material. In this deck you need to play lots of interruptions such as ash to stop your effects being negated and to stop your opponent making unstoppable boards with lots of negates. That's all you really need to know but that's not the only combos you can do with it but I feel like you need to find some out on your own. One more thing I've play tested this deck out many times on nexus and went 5:0 with this deck on there so I know its competitive and is a very strong rouge deck.

deck_name: Eldlich Dogmatika Invoked with a Bahamut Engine
deck_description: Bahamut combo:  Summon endymion, equip artemis  artemis search crowley  crowley send artemis, sp summon  crowley eff change to water  overlay into bahamut, summon toad           Edit: Added Eldland, removed imperm  Edit 2: Removed 1 al and invocation, added 2 meltdown

You have basically to activate Necrovalley and Spiritualist as soon as possible. You use Supernaturalist effect in order to add Necrovalley Throne (or Imperial Tombs if you already have Throne in hand) in EP. Next turn you just use Throne to add Gravekeeper's Headman, and use Headman's effect in order to summon Spiritualist again. You can now summon another Supernaturalist or link summon Verte Anaconda, in order to get Dragoon or Starving Venom Fusion Dragon, using SuperPoly.  I added Malefic Stardust Dragon cause it protects Necrovalley, and you can use it to summon Anaconda. Double Summon is also for Anaconda. If you have Recruiter on the field you can summon Artemis, triggering its effect. So you can add Commandant (in case you don't have Necrovalley on the field) or Spiritualist. Summon Black Rose Dragon (with Ash) if you want to clean the field. There's no Royal Tribute cause it's good only if you draw it in turn one imho, but you can add it in Side. SuperPolys and Storming Mirror Force in Side are for Dragoon.  I think this is the best Gravekeeper's deck ever built. Even if it's still a really slow-paced deck, it's a good antimeta, and it's also pretty simple to play.
Testing

deck_excerpt: My revamped Blackwing wing deck with new combos and dragoon
deck_description: New Blackwing deck that can end on a strong board with a variety of hands.     Combo 1-Strongest     Requires Blackwing - Simoon the Poison Wind, any Level 4 special summon, and any special summon. I’m using Blackwing - Kris the Crack of Dawn and Blackwing - Gale the Whirlwind.    Ends on Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon, Number 24: Dragulas the Vampiric Dragon, Time Thief Redoer with trap attached, Phantom Knights of Rusty Bardiche, Borreload Savage Dragon, and a Phantom Knight’s Fogblade.     Use Simoon effect in hand and banish Kris. Summon Simoon to search and activate Black Whirlwind. Use Whirl effect to search Blackwing – Auster the South Wind. Normal summon it to summon banished Kris. Use whirl effect to search Blackwing - Harmattan the Dust and special summon it. Use Simoon and Dust to make Raidraptor - Wise Strix. Activate its effect to summon Blackwing - Zephyros the Elite from the deck. Use Kris and Zephyros to make Force Strix and use its effect to get any monster other than Auster. I’ll use Blackwing - Bora the spear. Summon it triggering Wise, letting you search Rank-Up-Magic Soul Shave Force. Use Force and Wise to make Bardiche and active its effect to send The Phantom Knights of Ancient Cloak to GY to set Phantom Knights of Shade Brigandine from the deck. Banish Cloak to search Phantom Knights of Silent Boots. Special summon Boots and Brigandine, then use Zephyros effect in gy to send Whirl back to the and to summon itself. Now summon Gale. Use the Brigandine and Zephyros to make Redoes also summon the other Blackwing that was in your hand. Use Auster and Bora to make Borreload savage dragon. Use boots and gale for Predaplant Verte Anaconda. Use Soul Shave to banish Force in GY to summon Dragulas. Banish boots in GY for to searcha Fogblade. Finally, actvate Verte to summon Dragoon and set Fogblade.     5 Negates and can take destruction.    Combo 2-Brick    You need 1 level 4 Special summon and 2 of any special summon. I’ll use Oroshi, Bora, and Dust.    Ends on Dragoon, Infinity, and Fogblade.    Summon all 3 monsters to make Wise using the 2 other monsters other than the level 4, using Wise effect to summon Zephyros. Use the 2 level 4 to make Force and use its effect to search a level 4 special summon. Ill use Kris and special summon him trigging Wise to search Soul Shave. Use Wise and Force for Bardiche and use its effect to send Cloak to the GY and search Brigandine. Use Soul Shave to banish Force in GY to summon Cyber Dragon Infinity or Dragulas. Banish cloak in the GY to search search Boots. Summon Boots and Brigandine, then use Zephyros effect in GY to send the trap back to hand to summon itself. Use boots and Zephyros to make Verte. Banish boots to search and set Fogblade and use Verte to summon Dragoon. Lastly, attach Verte to Infinity.    3 negates is not great, but good for a brick.    Combo 3-Brick on Zephyros    Simmon and Zephyros are needed.    Ends Ultimate Falcon or Redoer and a Fogblade.    Use Simoon effect in hand to banish Zephyros, getting Whirl. Normal summon Simoon to trigger Whirl to search Auster. Summon Auster to summon the banished Zephyros and use Whirl to summon Dust (chain link 1 Auster, chain link 2 Whirl). Use Simmon and Auster to make Blackwing – Full Armor Master and use the rest to make Wise Strix. Use its effect to summon a any level 4. I’ll use Kris. Summon Zephyros from GY by sending Whirl to the hand and use that and Kris to make Force Strix and use its effect to search anything(I’ll use Raidraptor – Strangle Lanius), triggering Wise to set Rank-Up-Magic Phantom Knight’s Force. Use Wise and Force for Bardiche and send Cloak to the GY to set Brigandine. Summon Brigandine and Strangle to make Force. Use Force effect to search any level 4 special summon and summon it. Use the Rank up to summon Arsenal Falcon, use its effect to summon a level 4. Use the 2 levels fours to summon either Redoer or Raider’s Knight, which can summon Arc Rebellion XYZ Dragon to a zone that Bardiche points, which can activate its effect to destroy Arsenal Falcon and summon Ultimate Falcon. Banish Boots to set Fogblade.  ​  Weak combo but the chances of getting a hand this bad are rare.    Combo 4-Standard    Simoon and any level 4 Blackwing are needed. I’ll use Bora.    Ends on Ultimate Falcon, Fogblade, Borreload Savage, and Infinity.    Use Simoon effect in hand to banish Bora. Search Whirl and activate it. Summon Simoon and search Auster with Whirl. Normal summon Auster to summon the banished Bora and search Dust with Whirl. Summon Dust and use it and Simoon for Wise, using its effect to summon Zephyros from deck. Use Zephyros and any level 4 besides from Auster on the field to summon Force and detach Zephyros to search any level 4 special. Summon it triggering Wise Trix to set Soul Shave from the deck. Use Zephyros effect in GY to send Whirl back to hand to summon itself. Using Force and Wise to summon Bardiche. Now using the 2 level fours besides from Auster on the field summon another Force Trix use its effect to get any level 4 special summon. Summon that card and use it with Auster to summon Borreload Savage. Then use Bardiche to send Boots to the GY to search Phantom Knight’s Rank-Up-Magic Force. Use boots effect in the grave to get a fogblade.  Now on your opponent’s turn activate phantom knight rank up to banish everything besides the Force Strix to summon Ultimate falcon and when it is your turn use soul to summon Infinity.    Very strong consistent combo.    Thanks for reading and leave suggestions in the comments.      Combo credit to Speed YGO and Yacine656

deck_name: Sacred Beast Deck by Destined Rivals ($30 Budget Yu-Gi-Oh! Deck)
deck_excerpt: A really playable and easy to learn version of a Sacred Beast deck for $30 using three copies of the structure deck with decent consistency.
deck_description:
Deck profile and strategy from Duelist Destiny: https://youtu.be/KNpbc7NOJC8 Duel (Win) vs. Familiar-Possessed (Loss) Deck showcasing the deck strategies in action: https://youtu.be/qTzNMfzvd5k General strategy is to open with Dark Beckoning Beast or Opening of the Spirit Gates to use either to search for the other. Then, with either, summon or activate to search for either Chaos Summoning Beast or Dark Summoning Beast from deck to hand. Use the extra normal summon of Dark Beckoning Beast immediately to summon the card you just searched, and activate the card effect to special summon either Hamon Lord of Striking Thunder or Raviel Lord of Phantasms from your hand or deck. Repeat this strategy as much as possible, and:
  • Activate Awakening of the Sacred Beasts as soon as possible so you can begin to accumulate life points when your opponent special summons. Try to get all three face up on field because they all activate.
  • Establish two Lord cards on the field with the above trap card to establish trap and spell negation.
  • Use Cerulean Skyfire as soon as possible when you have Hamon on the field to establish spell or trap negation.
  • Banish Chaos Summoning Beast from your grave as early as possible to get Fallen Paradise from deck to hand and activate that after you have a lord card on field for it to become your Pot of Greed every turn.
  • Use Terraforming to preferably search Mound of the Bound Creator mid to late game since you can search Fallen Paradise
  • Use Field Barrier to lock in your field spell after you have cleared any opponent field spell with Mystical Space Typhoon
  • Use Uria Lord of Searing Flames for Fusion Summon of Armatyle only
  • Don't forget to use the token effect of Raviel
  • Use Shimmering Scraper (Raviel) to grant your real Raviel 8000 attack and multiple attacks to clear your opponents board
  • Don't fusion summon Armatyle without Dimension Fusion Destruction, otherwise he won't gain the effect of not taking battle damage (protecting your life points), and make sure you have Mound of the Bound activated at this point in the game. He's not protected by Fallen Paradise
Rinse and repeat strategies. Deck profile and strategy from Duelist Destiny: https://youtu.be/KNpbc7NOJC8 Duel (Win) vs. Familiar-Possessed (Loss) Deck showcasing the deck strategies in action: https://youtu.be/qTzNMfzvd5k

deck_excerpt: A Dragon Link deck that focuses on Resource Management Extenders, Negates, Disruptions, an Extra deck lock and a Graveyard lock.
deck_description: A semi-simple Dragon Link list, that doesn't go for superheavy combo plays to summon VFD (aka the Very Fun Dragon, konami please ban this very toxic card), but concentrates on resource Management and putting up a board with consistently.   This Deck is a meta deck with 60 cards (which can be cut down) with 38 monsters [of with there are 1 pendulum and 7 had traps (feel free to swap them out with other hand traps/generic spells & traps) and 18 spells that focus on negates (Applause and Savage), extenders, disruptions (hand traps and some spells), extra deck lock (Seal --> goliath, I suggest having Harbinger on the field to protect the goliath) and graveyard lock (union carrier + Wizard Buster)   Some main Endboards are: Seal + Savage (4) + Appolusa (3-4) Seal + Savage (4) + Borrelsword Seal + Savage (4) + Harbringer Seal + Harbringer + Savage (3) + Union Carrier Seal + Savage (4) + Abomination

deck_name: Dark Magician ft. Eldlich (can actually win)
deck_excerpt: Dark Magician and Eldlich actually have some synergy together!
deck_description: Dark Magician and Eldlich actually have some synergy together! You can use golden lord to send circle or combination to the graveyard to summon it back to the field! The main goal of the Dark magician engine is to boost out Dragoon. Magician's souls also synergizes very well with eldlich. The Dark Magicians can also be used to set Eldlich traps to the field!! You can also use Eldlich the Mad Golden Lord, Accesscode, Black Luster or even Dragoon to OTK the opponent. A typical end board should be Dragoon, Golden lord and a bunch of backrow. Overall a very fun deck to play and can also win duels! Have fun!! Suggestions in the comments.

deck_excerpt: My take on the Mermail/Atlantean deck that's been making a comeback lately.
deck_description: You've probably seen this deck in action before/have a fair understanding of strategies due to its popularity on youtube recently. These ratios work best for me!

Summon 2 Warrior Monsters. Link Summon Isolde, search any Warrior you do not need. Mill 4 Equip Spells (Phoenix Blade and 3 others except D.D.R) SS Armageddon Knight or Raiden (depends if Arma was summoned already) - > Link SUmmon Halqi. SS Deskbot. Link Summon Auroradon with Deskbot and Halqi. SS 3 Tokens, ss Deskbot from GY Synchro Summon Tool Dragon. Search D.D.R with Tool Dragon send Tool dragon and another token to GY for Coltwing SS 2 Token ss Deskbot from GY. Banish Arma from GY for Phoenix Blade. SS Arma with Diff. Mill Zephyros. Bounce DDR SS Zephyros Return a card back to ss Plague (if it was Milled by Arma if it was ss by Isolde). Synchro SUmmon Borreload Savage. equip it with Isolde. Otherwise you can also go to Apollousa or Bardiche

deck_excerpt: Evil Eye control deck, Serziel stun with some combos, built to take advantage of Pot of Prosperity.
deck_description: Evil Eye list, Serziel control with some Zerziel shenanigans for when Pot of Prosperity/Disparity is released. I cut Awakening and Catoblepas route out of the deck, since it isn't as strong as the Re-emergence/Basilius side. Made room for Torrential, cut a couple floodgates for Evenly for going second, cut a Defeat, trusting in Torrential to be good enough. Still running Sanctum and Scythe. Running Ash as the hand trap of choice, with a bunch of flexible going second cards to pick from in the side deck, + some Solemns. I like Judgement more personally, and it would be nice to nab those Feather Dusters etc, but Strike is having more success in the meta, so I'mma be lame and run those.

deck_excerpt: A combo-based strategy utilizing the new Vampire Dracula card for free summons to get into Skull Dread/Accesscode.
deck_description: Combining two of my favorite decks to form a combo-based strategy utilizing the new Vampire Dracula card.  You mostly want to summon it to get your opponent's monsters for a free Vampire Sheridan or use it for the link-4 monsters to end the game.  Highly versatile, can play through some negates, and easy to edit for your unique playstyle.   The only hand traps are in the side deck minus the one Called by the Grave in the main deck which can be changed up to whatever you prefer, but I definitely recommend Called by the Grave to play through your opponent's negate on Uni-Zombie/Gozuki.  The only expensive card as of posting is Accesscode Talker; if you can't afford it, then you can supplement it with a Borrelsword Dragon instead.  If you have any suggestions, criticism, or praise lemme know down below!  Starting to get back into Yugioh after a good hiatus, and wanted to start fresh with one of my favorite archetypes.  UPDATE 1/31/21: I nixed Borreload Savage Dragon and replaced it with the new link 5 monster Underworld Goddess of the Closed World since having monsters on the field is no issue, plus linking away your opponent's monster (especially a link-2 hit) is highly favorable, and easier overall to summon vs. savage dragon.  I also changed some sideboard cards after playtesting.  UPDATE 3/25/21: I changed around the side deck as well as adding Zeus to the mix in place of Sunsaga.  For some reason one of my side deck cards isn't showing up on the site here.  The last card in my side deck is Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon.

deck_name: For-Fun Red-Eyes Archetype Deck (with cards I actually own)
deck_excerpt: Summon Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon and profit. Oh, and some other cards too that you probably don't need, but makes a Red-Eyes player feel good.
deck_description: This deck is mostly for personal reference. I'm addicted to making deck lists to pass the time. Help me.  I would've labeled this deck as a fun/ casual deck, but the inclusion of Dark Dragoon makes that description null. Even so, it is not the most optimal Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon deck, as you can obviously tell from the deck list. My goal was to make a for-fun Red-Eyes Black Dragon archetype deck, sticking as closely to the archetype as possible, and using only cards that I actually owned, instead of the hypothetical deck lists posted to the site. This is why Cards of the Red Stone and Allure of Darkness are at 2x instead of 3x (I only own 2 of each), and why I don't have Upstart Goblin, Raigeki (I instead use Dark Hole as a pretend-Raigeki since it doesn't affect Dark Dragoon, and it keeps the deck in-line with the "Dark" theme), Harpie's Feather Duster, Pot of Desires, or Cosmic Cyclone. It's also why Dragoon is at 1 instead of 3, because I'm not spending 80-100$ on two more copies.  I understand a lot of these cards are unnecessary. Dark Dragoon is the win condition, but I wanted to have a fun deck that allowed for strategies outside the honestly brain-dead strategy of "draw or search for Red-Eyes Fusion, profit". That's why I have kinky-byo to let me summon Beast-Eyes Pendulum Dragon, to further make use of my level 1 monsters, Claw of Hermos to let me summon Red-Eyes Black Sword, and why I have 3 copies of the Darkness Metal link monster that I'll never ever summon (I consider those cards my deck cheerleaders). Staying inside the boundaries of an archetype gives me a warm and fuzzy feeling.

deck_excerpt: My take on a half competitive-half casual Adamancipators that attempts to summon Dragun of Red-Eyes and Borreload Savage Dragon then create game endin
deck_description: The goal of the deck is to turbo Borreload Savage Dragon and Dragun of Red-Eyes, Optimal opening would be a lvl 4 rock, Adamancipator Researcher and Adamancipator Seeker. Normal the lvl 4 rock -> Activate Researcher -> activate Analyzer. Use the effect of Researcher and Analyzer you are looking to hit Adamancipator Crystal Dragite to draw a card or Koa'Ki Mieru Guardian to protect board. Synchro into Adamancipator Risen Raptite to special a rock from top 5. Link 2 for Crystron Halqifibrax to special Researcher or Seeker. Link 2 for Predaplant Verte Anaconda using Halqifibrax. Synchro into Borreload then equip Halqifibrax. Activate Verte Anaconda to send Red-Eyes Fusion, Red-Eyes Black Dragon and Dark Magician from the deck to the graveyard. The Fossil Fusions are used to create beaters in the grind game or to make a material on the field for linking. A 2 card combo would be Miracle Rupture and Adamancipator Signs. Use Rupture to send Dragite from deck to grave and then use signs to Special Dragite from the GY. Use the effects to add Researcher or Seeker to the top of the deck then draw with Dragite to start your combo. Problems are bricking with Dragun materials and not finding a rock monster with Researcher or Seeker.

deck_description: The Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game Known as the Yu-Gi-Oh! Official Card Game (遊☆戯☆王オフィシャルカードゲーム, Yū-Gi-Ō Ofisharu Kādo Gēmu) in Asia, is a Japanese collectible card game developed and published by Konami. It is based on the fictional game of Duel Monsters created by manga artist Kazuki Takahashi, which is the main plot device during the majority of the manga franchise, Yu-Gi-Oh, and its various anime adaptations and spinoff series. "Adamancipator", known in Japan as "Adamassiah" (アダマシア Adamashia), is an archetype of Rock monsters which debuted in Deck Build Pack: Secret Slayers. It is a Synchro Archetype comprised of mostly Level 4 monsters of different attributes and two Level 2 EARTH monsters. They are used by Anna Des in Yu-Gi-Oh! OCG Structures. deck_description: The secret spice of this list is running a very small PK engine with Rusty to put up two Fog Blades negates. The trade-off is you lose 2 Apollousa negates, but with the amount of monster negates running around, losing this doesn't really matter (besides, a two mat Apollousa isn't that great anyway)  The new line is to use Elpy and Pisty to make Dillingerous dragon, then use Dill and the monster summoned off Pisty (or whatever other monster you have, but try to keep Rokket Tracer alive otherwise you can't make Savage) to make Rusty. This gets Dill into the graveyard which can then be resurrected to make Verte Anaconda off Rokket Tracer's effect.

deck_excerpt: Made some changes to one of pend god trif's recent deck profiles... thoughts? Would appreciate any helpful comments.
deck_description: Trif's original deck profile ran 3 of "Mythical Beast Master Cerberus", but recently I found that it would often brick in my hands, and even if I started with it, it usually wasn't even protected when it had those 4 spell counters on it, so I replaced 2 of them with Jester Confits. Additionally: Magister and Mythical Institution often became bricks in my hand, and running Desires at 3 was a disaster when I'd have multiple copies in my starting hand, so I took out one of each and added in 1 Black Fang Magician and 2 Purple Poisons. Since this added a lot more DARK monsters to my deck, I replaced "Into the Void" with 1 "Allure of Darkness", because I didn't like the discard effect of the former.  For the extra deck, I changed it so often that I don't remember exactly what was in Trif's original? I think it had 3 Selene? I replaced 1 of them with a Thousand-Eyes Restrict which I would sometimes use in place of Millennium-Eyes whenever I played Instant Fusion, depending on my situation (though it would usually still be Millennium-Eyes more often than not). In place of Appollousa I added 1 Abyss Dweller because of all the L4 Monsters I added in and because even when I would set up a fairly decent board with a good handful of negates, the sheer the amount of floating effects from some of these meta-decks I've been facing are still able to play through the negates and then still overwhelm me.  Anyways I'm still a novice when it comes to pendulums and deck building in general, if you guys know any cards I should switch out for better combos/consistency, please do tell me. Thanks.

deck_excerpt: Holy Night is 2 cards combo Seiyaryu control by itself using another LIGHT fairy, while the LIGHT fairies we run are able to pump VFD, Artifact Scythe
deck_description: https://youtu.be/25COCysupac We only take the Seiyaryu turbo as an engine, because playing Holy Night as a whole sucks. The engine is 2 Seiyaryu (easily searchable, play 2 as backup), 3 Rayel (add Bellfire/Nativity), 3 Bellfire (add Seiyaryu/Rayel), 3 Nativity (add/ss Seiyaryu from hand). So, basically this Seiyaryu turbo needs Nativity+1 LIGHT fairy. Some Holy Night card we could play for recovery is Flamel (recur Seiyaryu from GY, niche battle disruption) and Advent (recur from GY/ss Seiyaryu from hand). Since Nativity needs LIGHT fairy fodder, it makes sense to play the LIGHT fairy good stuff. Diviner is 1 card VFD by sending Trias Hierarchia, use Trias tribute Diviner, use Diviner ss Valkyrie Sechste, use Sechste ss Sigrun, make VFD. Artifact is good too since they're impactful fairies and also Nativity shuffles back the fairies, it means we don't have to run multiple copies of garnet. Eva is there as we can summon it through Diviner and it gives us Herald of The Orange Light with its effect online. We are able to run Extravagance as we dont need many extra deck monster to play. The recursion line depends on several cards only, like Trias (it wont banish itself if used in VFD), Holy Night Flamel/Advent, and Eva. We don't run another lv7 LIGHT dragon as they're all bad cards and we need fairy fodder for Nativity, not dragon. Pros: Unique playstyle with strong lock like VFD/Scythe. Cons: The recursion and end board are weak.

deck_excerpt: cards like Melffy puppie and Alpha, the master of beasts
deck_description: The best way to play is to hope you draw a starter card such as rescue cat played at 3 nimble beaver played at 3 or obedience schooled played at 3 but if u don't which is highly unlikely then rely on the melffy cards such as and the best one melffy puppie played at 3. Next if you get a starter card xyz into melffy of the forest played at 2 in extra and use the cards effect to add a melffy monster spell or trap from deck to your hand. I recommend melffy tag if you don't already have it in your hand or a monster like puppie if you dont have it all ready or the trap which gives u some interruption on your opponent. Then youse your melffy which you should have in hand either by adding it with melffy of the forest effect or by having it already in hand to special summon any melffy from grave which you should have because of the detaching of the unit from melffy of the forest. Then you can only do this next step if you used obedience schooled as your starter or you haven't normal summoned for turn. normal a second starter/extender or any melffy monster from hand to xyz again into a card appropriate for the situation either going first or second. If your going first I would go into joyous melffys and just stool out. By the way you really want to go second with this deck. If you are going second I say you should wipe the opponents board by using Alpha,  the master of beasts but remember to leave some monsters on your side and also its not a once per turn effect. Also i recomend attacking in some way with an xyz monster at some point in your first turn to make Divine arsenal. then just youse you melffys effects from hand and field at end phases and on the field any time you think you need to disrupt your opponent. The small combo i would youse is if your opponent summons a monster that can be destroyed by card effect and its causing you a real problem then use puppies effect from field to bounce itself back to hand to summon Kalantosa  which will destroy it when special summoned. That's really about it I feel like if you want to use this deck you need to come up with some off your own combos with it its more fun that way. Have fun with the deck and tell me how it goes on Instagram which is lukepastone :)
